            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;img src=&quot;http://www.chinafaqs.org/files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/china%20air%20pollution%202.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; title=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;180&quot; height=&quot;120&quot; class=&quot;imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default&quot;/&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    Jonathan Moch        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given the health risks posed by air pollution, it is easy to understand why the Chinese government wants to address this problem. However, the dilemma is that some steps to clean up air pollution can actually contribute to global warming.&lt;/p&gt;
